{"parts":[{"text":"I have access to a variety of tools and can delegate tasks to specialized agents to help you with different requests.\n\nHere's a detailed description:\n\n**My Built-in Tools:**\n\n1.  **Date/Time Tool (`get_current_datetime`):**\n    *   **Purpose:** To fetch the current date, time, and day of the week.\n    *   **Use Cases:** When you ask \"What time is it?\", \"What's today's date?\", or \"What day is it?\".\n\n2.  **Expense Tracker Tools:**\n    *   **Purpose:** To manage your financial expenses.\n    *   **Tools:**\n        *   `add_expense_tool(date, amount, category, note, subcategory)`: Adds a new expense record with details like date, amount, category, and an optional note or subcategory.\n        *   `edit_expense_tool(expense_id, amount, category, date, note, subcategory)`: Modifies an existing expense record identified by its ID. You can update any of its fields.\n        *   `delete_expense_tool(expense_id)`: Removes an expense record using its unique ID.\n        *   `search_expenses_tool(category, end_date, max_amount, min_amount, start_date)`: Allows you to search for expenses based on various filters such as category, date range (start and end date), or amount range (minimum and maximum amount).\n\n3.  **To-Do List Tools:**\n    *   **Purpose:** To help you create, manage, and track your tasks and reminders.\n    *   **Tools:**\n        *   `add_task_tool(title, description, due_date, priority)`: Creates a new task with a title, optional description, due date, and priority (e.g., high, medium, low).\n        *   `edit_task_tool(task_id, title, description, due_date, priority, status)`: Updates an existing task by its ID. You can change its title, description, due date, priority, or status (e.g., 'pending', 'in-progress', 'completed').\n        *   `delete_task_tool(task_id)`: Deletes a task using its ID.\n        *   `complete_task_tool(task_id)`: Marks a specified task as completed.\n        *   `search_tasks_tool(due_date, priority, status)`: Searches for tasks based on filters like due date, priority, or status.\n\n4.  **File System Tools:**\n    *   **Purpose:** To interact with the local file system, allowing for file and directory management.\n    *   **Tools:**\n        *   `read_file_tool(file_path)`: Reads the content of a specified file.\n        *   `write_file_tool(file_path, content)`: Writes content to a file, overwriting existing content if the file exists.\n        *   `edit_file_tool(file_path, old_text, new_text)`: Finds and replaces specific text within a file.\n        *   `append_file_tool(file_path, content)`: Adds content to the end of a specified file.\n        *   `copy_file_tool(source_path, destination_path)`: Copies a file from one location to another.\n        *   `move_file_tool(source_path, destination_path)`: Moves a file from a source to a destination path.\n        *   `delete_file_tool(file_path)`: Deletes a specified file.\n        *   `clear_file_tool(file_path)`: Clears all content from a file, leaving it empty.\n        *   `create_directory_tool(folder_path)`: Creates a new directory (folder).\n        *   `delete_directory_tool(folder_path, recursive)`: Deletes a directory. Can also delete non-empty directories if `recursive` is set to True.\n        *   `rename_directory_tool(source_path, destination_path)`: Renames a directory.\n        *   `list_files_tool(folder_path)`: Lists all files within a specified directory.\n        *   `list_directories_tool(folder_path)`: Lists all subdirectories within a specified directory.\n        *   `list_tree_tool(folder_path, max_depth)`: Displays the directory structure as a tree, with an optional maximum depth.\n        *   `file_info_tool(file_path)`: Provides information about a file (e.g., size, last modified date).\n        *   `supported_formats_tool()`: (Currently not implemented in the provided tools, but typically would list supported file formats for certain operations).\n\n**Specialized Agents (Delegated via `transfer_to_agent`):**\n\n1.  **Research Agent (`research_agent`):**\n    *   **Purpose:** To perform in-depth research on any given topic, whether it's technical, factual, news-related, or scientific. It uses parallel web searches to gather information.\n    *   **When I use it:** When your query requires comprehensive information gathering from the web, such as \"What are the latest developments in AI?\", \"Explain quantum physics\", or \"Find news about climate change.\"\n\n2.  **Problem Solver Agent (`problem_solver_agent`):**\n    *   **Purpose:** Specializes in analyzing and debugging programming errors, exceptions, stack traces, bugs, configuration issues, and other technical problems. It identifies root causes and provides step-by-step solutions, often leveraging Google Search for common fixes.\n    *   **When I use it:** *Crucially*, I transfer to this agent whenever your message contains any form of error message, traceback, bug description, or asks for help with debugging or fixing code. For example, \"I'm getting a TypeError in my Python script, can you fix it?\", or \"My application is crashing with this stack trace...\".\n\n3.  **Python Agent (`python_agent`):**\n    *   **Purpose:** To apply specific modifications, fixes, refactorings, or new features to a provided Python script. It takes the original script and instructions for changes and returns the updated script.\n    *   **When I use it:** *Crucially*, I transfer to this agent when you provide a Python script (usually in a code block) and ask me to modify it in any way, such as \"Add a new function to this script,\" \"Refactor this class,\" or \"Apply this patch to the code below.\"\n\nI will choose the most appropriate tool or agent based on your request to provide you with the best assistance.","thought_signature":"CpwEAb4-9vvKpXSVK7JBrScL7psDDf3W5Sg9eRab_u5WMW-yet8sGUyMzhfPKPYQaABaPLGTgn55uDug4KrT5dPFN6oWZQBZrHytKEVhgxW1W9ggRUxPDHy5iEjska-CgfrbLG4Yr1o6d3GFKGNLJx_eUCZxeEWRmWjFtxnYwu9r